nd analysis.\n","\n","### Daily Average\n","\n","Before starting analysis, I decided to rename the data frames to something easier to work with. And while not necessary, for sake of ease and consistency, I made the column names all lower case.\n","\n","Next, I want to find out the average of all measurable columns (i.e. TotalSteps, TotalDistance, etc). First I'll start with the 'dailyActivity_merged' data set, or as I've called it, 'd2'.\n","\n","Since there are 30 unique participants, I wanted to find the daily average per user but also of the users as a whole group. I aggregated the individuals and rounded down to 2 decimal spots for readability."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":2,"id":"2ce019e7","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2023-10-05T13:40:31.891664Z","iopub.status.busy":"2023-10-05T13:40:31.850457Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-10-05T13:40:31.947158Z","shell.execute_reply":"2023-10-05T13:40:31.945381Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.109864,"end_time":"2023-10-05T13:40:31.950447","exception":false,"start_time":"2023-10-05T13:40:31.840583","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["d2 <- read.csv('/kaggle/input/capstonedata/dailyActivity_merged.csv')\n","names(d2) <- tolower(names(d2))\n","avgdaily <- aggregate(d2[,3:15], list(d2$id), mean)\n","rd2 <- round(avgdaily, digits=2)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"3608b204","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.00801,"end_time":"2023-10-05T13:40:31.967054","exception":false,"start_time":"2023-10-05T13:40:31.959044","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["Below is a table previewing the top-10 results sorted by total steps in descending order."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b527b06d","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.007601,"end_time":"2023-10-05T13:40:31.982359","exception":false,"start_time":"2023-10-05T13:40:31.974758","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["<p>\n","<table>\n","   \n","<colgroup>\n","<col style=\"width: 7%\" />\n","<col style=\"width: 7%\" />\n","<col 